element.name: finite-length warburg (open)
element.description: A diffusion-induced impedance element. Similar to the warburg impedance, this element has a 45-degree phase angle at high frequencies. At low frequencies, this element behaves like a capacitor. The difference is the fact that the diffusion layer now has a finite thickness, beyond which the solute cannot diffuse through. The characteristic time constant of this element, T, has the expression: T=L^2/D, where L is the characteristic thickness of the diffusion layer, and D is the diffusivity of the diffusing species
